title: Man United vs Southampton: Jose Mourinho makes six changes at Wembley | Metro News
text:
Sean Kearns for Metro.co.uk Sunday 26 Feb 2017 3:22 pm Jose Mourinho is aiming to make history at Wembley (Picture: Getty) 
Jose Mourinho has made six changes to his starting XI for Manchester United’s EFL Cup final clash with Southampton. 
The 54-year-old is looking to join Sir Alex Ferguson and Brian Clough on four League Cups with a victory at Wembley. Jurgen Klopp sends warning to his Liverpool flops after Leicester loss 
Henrikh Mkhitaryan sustained a hamstring injury against St Etienne and fails to make the side’s 18-man squad with Jesse Lingard coming in for the Armenian. 
Juan Mata was a doubt for the game but the Spaniard starts at Wembley, where he scored a crucial goal for United in their FA Cup final win against Crystal Palace last May. 
The likes of Daley Blind, Ashley Young and Marouane Fellaini have all lost their places following on from the 1-0 win against St Etienne with Anthony Martial, Jesse Lingard and Marcos Rojo starting.
